<p class="p">
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm16" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">f</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the volume fraction of phase
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm17" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mspace width="4pt" class="mspace"/>
     <mi class="mi">x</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> and
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm18" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mspace width="4pt" class="mspace"/>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">v</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the flow velocity in the
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm19" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mspace width="4pt" class="mspace"/>
     <mi class="mi">i</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>-th element.
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm20" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mspace width="4pt" class="mspace"/>
     <mi class="mi">N</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the elements that the cross-section of the pipe is divided into with an equal area
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm21" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mspace width="4pt" class="mspace"/>
     <mi class="mi">a</mi>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. The tomography technology is illustrated in 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="sensors-19-02184-f004" class="xref">Figure 4</xref>, where two series of images are taken simultaneously. Each series are representing a cross-section of the pipe, which are cross-correlated to obtain the velocity profile
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm22" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mspace width="4pt" class="mspace"/>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">v</mi>
      <mi class="mi">i</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>. The volume fraction distribution of the phase
 <inline-formula class="inline-formula">
  <math id="mm23" class="math">
   <mrow class="mrow">
    <mrow class="mrow">
     <mspace width="4pt" class="mspace"/>
     <msub class="msub">
      <mi class="mi">f</mi>
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <mi class="mi">i</mi>
       <mo class="mo">(</mo>
       <mi class="mi">x</mi>
       <mo class="mo">)</mo>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> can be obtained directly by the images provided from the tomographic sensors [
 <xref rid="B56-sensors-19-02184" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">56</xref>].
</p>
